Whonix News File Format
Version 0.1

First line contains version and may not contain any spaces!

Between the ########## is an example news file.
Drop the ########## from the whonix_news file.

##########
0.3.0

news text here
some more news text
...
#########

How to create a valid Whonix News File:
1. safe as whonix_news
2. sign: gpg --clearsign whonix_news
3. test: gpg --verify whonix_news.asc

Extra implementation info:

/usr/local/bin/whonixcheck will find out the current installing version by:

# Read only FIRST line.
read -r INSTALLED_WHONIX_VERSION < /usr/share/whonix/version
# Remove ALL spaces.
INSTALLED_WHONIX_VERSION="${INSTALLED_WHONIX_VERSION//[[:space:]]}"

